                <h1>"Understanding 'Una Vez': Preterite vs. Imperfect Tense"</h1>
                <p>"Una vez" can be used in the preterite tense, indicating a completed action in the past, such as "Fui una vez al cine." In contrast, the imperfect tense describes ongoing or habitual actions in the past. It's important to choose the right tense based on the narrative context to convey the appropriate meaning in Spanish.</p>
